data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":197,"item_id":"msg_0599eb1eb2a9556f0069337706a74c8190adfc446136ca09f2","output_index":2,"content_index":0,"text":"Contoso Electronics has established a Whistleblower Policy to maintain a safe and transparent working environment. This policy encourages employees and associated parties to report any unethical or illegal activities they witness. Key elements of the policy include:\n\n- **Definition**: A whistleblower is someone who reports activities that are illegal, unethical, or not in accordance with company policy.\n  \n- **Reporting Procedures**: Reports can be made by contacting the Human Resources Department, emailing the Compliance Officer at compliance@contoso.com, or calling the Compliance Hotline at 1-800-555-1212. Anonymous reports are also accepted through the hotline.\n\n- **Retaliation Prohibited**: Any retaliation against whistleblowers is strictly prohibited and can result in disciplinary action, up to termination.\n\n- **Confidentiality**: The identity of the whistleblower is kept confidential as permitted by law.\n\n- **Investigation**: All reports are investigated promptly and thoroughly .","logprobs":[]}

